\pard\f0\fs28  Plants from W. Hungary, S.E. Austria and N. Jugoslavia, with revolute leaf-margins and a rather erect habit, have been described as forma{\b  arbusculoides} Tuzson,{\i  Bot. Közl.}{\b  10}: 151 (1911). This occurs only on acid soils and may, perhaps, deserve recognition as a subspecies.
