\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. D. gnidioides} Jaub. & Spach,{\i  Ill. Pl. Or.}{\b  4}: 4 (1850). Erect shrub; branches long, strict, stout; young shoots pubescent with brown hairs. Leaves 25-40 × 4-7 mm, oblong-lanceolate, cuspidate-acuminate, pungent, erect, sessile, coriaceous, glaucous, with a few appressed hairs when young, glabrous later. Flowers pink, subsessile, in terminal, ebracteate heads of 5-8 and also in clusters of 2-3 in the upper leaf-axils. Hypanthium broad, covered with silky hairs. Sepals oblong, obtuse, 1/2-2/3 as long as the hypanthium. Drupe with coriaceous, scarcely fleshy exocarp, enclosed in the hypanthium till ripe.{\i  Aegean region }({\i Skiathos, Evvoia, Astipalaia}). Gr. ({\i E. Aegean and S. Anatolia}.)
